L(θ)=1m∑i=1mri2(θ)=1m∑i=1mri(θ)Tri(θ)=e(θ)Te(θ)\begin{aligned}
L(\theta) &= \frac{1}{m} \sum_{i=1}^{m} r_{i}^{2}(\theta) = \frac{1}{m} \sum_{i=1}^{m}  r_{i}(\theta)^T r_{i}(\theta)\\
 &= e(\theta)^T e(\theta)\\
\end{aligned}

